==English==
===Etymology===
From the Arabic {{ARchar|[[عدن]]}} (''ʕadn''), [[Eden]].

===Proper noun===
'''Aidenn'''
# Paradise.

===Quotations===
*"Tell this soul with sorrow laden if, within the distant '''Aidenn''' / It shall clasp a sainted maiden whom the angels named Lenore" (The Raven [http://www.heise.de/ix/raven/Literature/Lore/TheRaven.html], E. A. Poe).

